about.summary: Transforms datetime data into a format ready for analysis. It offers two core functionalities; aggregating data to a higher level interval (thicken) and imputing records where observations were absent (pad).

name: r-padr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.5.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-padr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/padr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/padr/padr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 40880f96697b896a956d8e6430c2b0135326aa726a52988ffeed39477f5493d1

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}      # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}        # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp
    - r-dplyr >=0.6.0
    - r-lubridate
    - r-rlang
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp
    - r-dplyr >=0.6.0
    - r-lubridate
    - r-rlang

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('padr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('padr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/EdwinTh/padr
  license: MIT
  summary: 'Transforms datetime data into a format ready for analysis. It offers two core functionalities;
    aggregating data to a higher level interval (thicken) and imputing records where
    observations were absent (pad). '
  license_family: MIT

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
